cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.SE 

The paper focuses on the security and privacy issues of Bitcoin, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). It also discusses the underlying blockchain technology, which can be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), as well as database management (cs.DB). The analysis of Bitcoin peer-to-peer network security risks and Bitcoin storage security can be classified under software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the discussion of alternative cryptocurrencies and emerging technologies can be categorized under computer networks and communications (cs.CY).
